  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with potentially significant legal consequences. Typically, if someone is caught laundering money, they may face:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Federal or state criminal prosecution\n- Potential felony charges\n- Possible prison time (often several years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Forfeiture of illegally obtained funds\n\n3. Additional consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding employment\n- Potential civil lawsuits\n\nThe specific punishment depends on the amount of money involved, jurisdiction, and individual circumstances. Consulting a legal professional would provide the most accurate information for a specific case.",
